title: Paceman Matthew Dunn signs new three-year deal with Surrey
text:
Paceman Matthew Dunn signs new three-year deal with Surrey 09 Oct 2015 16:16:56 
comments 
Surrey fast bowler Matthew Dunn has become the latest player to commit his future to the Kia Oval club. 
Dunn, who took 28 wickets in nine LV= County Championship appearances at 35.14 this summer, has signed a new three-year deal, keeping him with the county until the end of the 2018 season. 
Surrey director of cricket Alec Stewart said: "Matt has continued his development nicely and will play a big role within our attack in all formats over the coming years." 
The 23-year-old joins the likes of Jason Roy, Tom Curran, Ben Foakes, Zafar Ansari and Rory Burns in extending his stay at Surrey. Related Sport News
